Premier League leaders Manchester City will travel to second-tier Championship side Peterborough United while Chelsea are away at Luton Town in the fifth round of the FA Cup after most of the top-flight sides avoided each other in Sundayâ€™s draw. City came from behind to beat Fulham 4-1 while Chelsea defeated Plymouth Argyle 2-1 in extra time on Saturday. Tottenham Hotspur, who saw off Brighton & Hove Albion 3-1, must travel to Middlesbrough, who beat Manchester United on penalties at Old Trafford. In an all-Premier League clash, Southampton host West Ham United who survived a potential upset at the hands of non-league side Kidderminster Harriers with last-gasp goals in normal time and extra time. Liverpool were rewarded with a home game against Norwich City after overcoming Cardiff City 3-1 on Sunday, while Nottingham Forest set up a clash against Huddersfield Town following a shock win over holders Leicester City. Elsewhere, Everton will host Boreham Wood after the non-league side-stunned Championship club Bournemouth 1-0 in the late game on Sunday. The fifth-round games will be played in the week commencing February 28.  FA Cup fifth round draw Luton Town vs Chelsea Crystal Palace vs Stoke City Peterborough vs Man City Liverpool vs Norwich City Saints vs West Ham Middlesbrough v Spurs Nottingham vs Huddersfield Everton v Boreham Wood 